The Mexican Secretariat of Commercehas told the U.S. that recent implementation of a 10 pct advalorem tariff for fixed vegetable oils, fluid or solid, crude,refined or purified, was not targeted at sunflower oil, theU.S. Agriculture Department said.    In its World Production and Trade Report, the departmentsaid the increase in tariffs on this category which includessunflower, corn and rapeseed oils, was a reaction to importersusing basket categories to avoid paying tariffs on specifichigh-tariff products. Reuter&#3;